description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are seeking a Cancer Nurse Specialist to join theOmnesHealthcare Family; become part of a company that makes a difference.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;£55,000.00 per annum pro rata&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Based in North Middlesex Hospital, North London&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;24 hours/week (including Fridays)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;We have fully COVID compliant infection control policies in place.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;OmnesHealthcare Limited are operating within the NHS to provide personalised, quality healthcare services and have been doing so since 2006. We aim to develop supportive, genuine relationships with every patient, physician, nurse and healthcare professional that we come into contact with. We believe each patient is unique and deserves treatment that is both effective, heartfelt and has a positive outcome on their well-being.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you join us, you&#39;ll be part of something special–an innovative and rapidly growing organisation where we know that the finest patient care comes from empowering our teams to be the very best at what they do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is the purpose of the position?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic, motivated Dermatology Cancer Nurse Specialist, with a demonstrable clinical interest within this specialist area, who can work independently in Nurse led and Consultant led clinics in the community. The emphasis of this position has four main areas of responsibility: Clinical, Educational, Management/Leadership and Research/Audit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What are the key responsibilities?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post holder is expected to provide a comprehensive service for patients with cancer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post holder will provide expert care, advice and support to patients with a suspected or confirmed cancer on an in-patient and out-patient basis, and to their families, and acts as a resource for other staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What do you need to join theOmnesHealthcare Family?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CurrentNMCRegistration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evidence of professional updating&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evidence of post-registration training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with minor operation procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MOP Trained&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WhatOmnesHealthcare will offer you in return?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;25 days holiday plus bank holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An extra day off to celebrate your birthday&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Discount&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;And other benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported by, and work with, a diverse multi-skilled professional team of clinical and non-clinical friendly staff. In return we offer sponsored training, flexible working , family friendly policies, career progression within an expanding organisation, a competitive salary and benefits package, including medical indemnity for all work undertaken forOmnesHealthcare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Apply today if you want to make a difference.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We believe in innovation; we believe in listening to everyone; we believe in providing quality service; and we believe our employees will help us achieve our mission.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please be aware that all communications about this vacancy will be received to you via email. Always check your mail box and junk mail folders and provide a UK mobile number if available.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
